The affine.for folder crashes when it runs inside dialect conversion. The test pass converts func.func to llvm.func, which detaches the old entry block while values inside the loop still point to the old block arguments. The old block has no parent region at this point, which is a known dialect conversion problem, see #89770. When the driver then tries to fold the affine.for, the loop yields one of these old block arguments, and the assertion in the folder calls isDefinedOutsideOfLoop on it. This dereferences the null parent region and segfaults. This patch adds a check before the assertion so the folder bails out when the value has no parent region. The loop cannot be folded in this state anyway, so the conversion driver leaves the op alone and the pass finishes without crashing. A regression test is added.
